<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>About - Student Management</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bulma@0.9.4/css/bulma.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/navbar') %>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="box">
        <h1 class="title is-2">Student Management System</h1>
        <p class="subtitle is-4">JSON-Based CRUD Application</p>
        
        <div class="content">
          <h3 class="title is-4">Features</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>‚úÖ <strong>Read</strong> - Display all students from JSON file</li>
            <li>‚úÖ <strong>Add</strong> - Add new students via form submission</li>
            <li>üîÑ <strong>Statistics</strong> - Calculate passing rate and averages</li>
            <li>üé® <strong>Responsive Design</strong> - Works on mobile and desktop</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="title is-4">Technologies Used</h3>
          <div class="columns">
            <div class="column">
              <div class="notification is-primary is-light">
                <p><strong>Backend</strong></p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Node.js</li>
                  <li>Express.js</li>
                  <li>fs module (file system)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column">
              <div class="notification is-info is-light">
                <p><strong>Frontend</strong></p>
                <ul>
                  <li>EJS Templates</li>
                  <li>Bulma CSS</li>
                  <li>HTML Forms</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column">
              <div class="notification is-success is-light">
                <p><strong>Data</strong></p>
                <ul>
                  <li>JSON Files</li>
                  <li>File-based storage</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3 class="title is-4">How Forms Work</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>User fills out the form on <code>/add-student</code></li>
            <li>Form submits via <strong>POST</strong> request to <code>/add-student</code></li>
            <li>Express receives form data using <code>express.urlencoded()</code> middleware</li>
            <li>Server reads existing <code>students.json</code> file</li>
            <li>New student is added to the array with auto-incremented ID</li>
            <li>Array is written back to <code>students.json</code></li>
            <li>User is redirected to home page to see updated list</li>
          </ol>

          <h3 class="title is-4">Key Code Snippets</h3>
          
          <h4>Form Submission (HTML)</h4>
          <pre><code>&lt;form action="/add-student" method="POST"&gt;
  &lt;input type="text" name="name" required&gt;
  &lt;input type="email" name="email" required&gt;
  &lt;button type="submit"&gt;Add Student&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</code></pre>

          <h4>Handling POST Request (Express)</h4>
          <pre><code>app.post('/add-student', (req, res) => {
  const students = readJSONFile('students.json');
  const newStudent = {
    id: students.length + 1,
    name: req.body.name,
    email: req.body.email
  };
  students.push(newStudent);
  writeJSONFile('students.json', students);
  res.redirect('/');
});</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="notification is-warning is-light">
          <p><strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Important Limitations:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>No validation</strong> - Data isn't validated before saving</li>
            <li><strong>No error handling</strong> - File errors could crash the server</li>
            <li><strong>Not concurrent-safe</strong> - Multiple writes at once could corrupt data</li>
            <li><strong>Not scalable</strong> - Reading/writing entire file on every request</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong>Solution:</strong> In Part 2, we'll use SQLite database which solves all these issues!
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="buttons">
          <a href="/" class="button is-primary">View Students</a>
          <a href="/add-student" class="button is-success">Add Student</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
